---- MODULE MCDieHarder ----
2tlax13/DieHarder.xhm9654078_extended  is a TLA+ module that extends the Die Hard problem with additional features and constraints to facilitate solving it using Model Checking tools like TLC or SPIN, providing more flexibility in specifying constants for model checking purposes within these tool configurations (such as Jug capacity).
2tlax13/DieHarder.xhm9654078_extended  defines a function MCCapacity that returns the maximum amount of water you can fill in one move based on which jugs are chosen to be emptied or filled, and substitutes this for Capcity within TLC configuration file via constants. The same applies with MCJug constant as well - it tells us about Jug capacity defined by user/modeler beforehand (like how much water can the most capable of a particular jug hold), then we tell model checkers to substitute these values into corresponding place in our configurations, effectively controlling what specific setups TLC is going through while searching for satisfying solutions.
2tlax13-xhm9654078_extended  also includes a NotSolved invariant that ensures the solution hasn't been found yet (if it has then there would be some combination of moves leading to goal state), thus helping TLC during its model checking process.
